  "content": "ncluding the new `test_docs_config_*` tests.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-common/src/config.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(config): add DocsConfig for workspace doc placement rules\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1.3: Add metadata filter fields to `RetrievalOpts`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_types.rs:8-23`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add filter fields to `RetrievalOpts`**\n\nIn `rag_types.rs`, add to the `RetrievalOpts` struct:\n\n```rust\npub struct RetrievalOpts {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    /// Filter results by content_role (post-filter, Option A from spec).\n    pub content_role: Option<String>,\n    /// Filter results by source_origin (post-filter, Option A from spec).\n    pub source_origin: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n\nUpdate the `Default` impl to include:\n\n```rust\ncontent_role: None,\nsource_origin: None,\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Verify defaults**\n\nAdd a quick assertion in the kernel test module or inline:\n\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn test_retrieval_opts_filter_defaults() {\n    let opts = RetrievalOpts::default();\n    assert!(opts.content_role.is_none());\n    assert!(opts.source_origin.is_none());\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Build and run test**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo build -p corvia-kernel && cargo test -p corvia-kernel test_retrieval_opts_filter -- --nocapture`\nExpected: Compiles and test passes.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_types.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(kernel): add content_role/source_origin filter fields to RetrievalOpts\"\n```\n\n---\n",
